What We Crimp

Pre-Crimped Wire Applications

Pre-crimped wires are used when you need ready-to-assemble wire leads with terminals already attached. Ideal for prototyping, mass production, and field installation.

Prototyping & Development

Rapid iteration with pre-terminated wires. Test circuits and configurations without manual crimping.

Mass Production Assembly

Speed up production lines with ready-to-install wire leads. Consistent quality, reduced labor.

Field Installation

Pre-crimped leads for on-site assembly. No crimping tools required at installation point.

Battery Connections

Battery pack assembly with pre-crimped leads. Reliable connections for BMS and power distribution.

Sensor Integration

Sensor cables with pre-crimped connectors. Quick connection to control systems and data acquisition.

LED Lighting

LED strip connections with pre-crimped wires. Simplify LED driver and power supply installation.

Configuration Options

Crimp Specifications

Choose from single-end or dual-end crimped configurations. Specify exact terminal types and wire specifications.

Single-End Crimped

One end crimped with terminal, other end stripped or tinned. Ready for soldering or terminal block connection.

  • ‚ñ∏ Terminal on one end only
  • ‚ñ∏ Other end stripped or tinned
  • ‚ñ∏ Cost-effective for board connections
  • ‚ñ∏ Custom wire lengths

Dual-End Crimped

Both ends crimped with terminals. Ready for immediate connector-to-connector assembly.

  • ‚ñ∏ Terminals on both ends
  • ‚ñ∏ Male-to-female or same-type
  • ‚ñ∏ Quick disconnect capability
  • ‚ñ∏ Wire-to-wire assemblies
